6:
Precisely, Varen! You've hit the
proverbial nail on the head!
Endeavor though we might to aid
our people, the shackles of our
noble birth bind us.
9:
I'm relieved to hear you agree with
me, Prince Razelt!
14:
I must apologize as well... I was told
that my presence on your trip would
be a burden, so I reluctantly
remained behind—reduced to a
glorified bench warmer!
18:
But here, in Starview Village, I can
bring my full arsenal of knowledge
to bear! Allow me to share some
delightful information with you.
22:
You've piqued my curiosity, Prince
Razelt! It would be an honor to
receive a lesson from you directly!
26: Well then, let us begin at once—
31:
H-here, a bit of reckless fun will not
escalate into an international
incident! S-such are the perks of
traveling to other worlds!
36: A-are you really sure about that?!
45: I believe we need to have a talk.
49:
Your Highness, with all due respect,
were you not aware of the high
position Prince Varen holds in the
line of succession?!
50:
Surely you realize the stakes of this
situation?! If the prince were to lose
his life here, our entire nation would
be plunged into chaos!
53:
B-but, I... I merely wanted to show
the younger generation the thrills
that Starview Village has to offer!
56:
You should know better than that,
Prince Razelt!
59: Come now, no need to be so harsh.
62:
I share some of the blame. I was
wrapped up in my dream of
pretending to be a common
adventurer. I deserve to be scolded
too!
65:
Indeed, Your Highness will be forced
to reflect upon his actions as well.
68:
*gulp* Y-Yuwel... Can you get me
out of this?
72:
Alk looks to be quite busy—I ought to
lend him a hand. Besides, I imagine
you'd prefer I didn't witness the
indignity of your scolding.
77:
Aren't knights supposed to help
people in their times of need?!
81:
Hah! It serves you right, Prince of
Dunces! I'd say you're long overdue
for a proper tongue-lashing.
84:
I mean, there's stupid, but then
there's endangering the life of Prince
Varen! A spectacular blunder, even
for you!
87:
Perhaps you're not in the best
position to criticize, Libram.
90:
If I recall, the responsibility for Prince
Varen's well-being lies entirely with
you.
95:
I... Now that you mention it! Azrail will
tear me to pieces if he hears of this,
won't he?!
100:
I'm so sorry! I'll make sure to
apologize to your brother, Prince
Libram.
104:
Looks like he's getting used to this
place.
107:
Yes... Though I'd prefer he not take
after Prince Razelt quite so much.
The two are already eerily similar in
character...
111:
Like two peas in a pod. But hey,
that's not always a bad thing.
122:
I'm sorry! I admit I was in the wrong,
so please just... spare me the rest!
There's something very unnerving
about being scolded by twins...
126:
Think it's about time we cast him a
lifeline?
129:
I'd say so, yeah. Poor kid's had
enough.
136:
Oh man, am I ever tired. I know it's
their job to lecture me, but that one
went on for AGES.
140:
A sign of how deeply they care for
you, no doubt. And I daresay they
aren't the only ones.
143:
Perhaps you're right... I made an
error in judgment. A person of my
station can't afford to be so reckless
and carefree.
146:
Your Highness, a messenger has
arrived from the homeland.
Someone has requested an urgent
audience with you.
149:
Well, if it isn't Varen! Thank you for
gracing me with your presence. It's
an honor to meet you!
151:
The honor is mine, Prince Arthram!
Your brother Prince Razelt is a dear
friend!
154:
Though I was surprised to hear you'd
come all this way to see me. To
what do I owe the pleasure?
156:
Haha... I couldn't pass up the
opportunity to speak to the prince
who saved our kingdom, now could
I? Tell me, how do you find Palpebra?
159:
It's incredible—full of so much to see
and do! Though I must admit, I'm
sometimes taken aback by how
different everything is.
162:
Of course, I realize that cultures
across the world differ... But even
then, Palpebra is something else
entirely.
164:
Indeed. Different though it may be,
our relationship with the city is
growing. We cannot afford to ignore
Palpebra.
165:
Would you agree with my
assessment, Prince Varen?
167:
Hmm... Perhaps. House Swes
certainly seems to agree with you—I
believe that's also been their policy.
170:
You know, I've become more
interested in viewing the bigger
picture as of late... It's actually a
surprising amount of fun!
173:
But beyond my own enjoyment, I
think it's necessary if one wishes to
be a ruler. This incident has only
strengthened that belief.
176:
Thinking as a ruler, are you? As you
should. I'm in complete agreement!
178:
Incidentally, I hear you've been
getting on well with my brother of
late. Is that right?
181:
Yes! He's been great to me. Prince
Razelt and I have been—
183:
Please put an end to that, won't
you? He doesn't need to be involved.
185:
Don't misunderstand, it's just—as
you no doubt know—my brother
doesn't have a mind for politics. It's
why he was sent away in the first
place.
188:
Prince Arthram... I have to say, you're
kind of scaring me.
191:
Aha! You have nothing to fear—I'm
not Prince Lornite of House Kwetur,
after all. You and I will get along just
fine. Won't we?
194:
Y-yes, of course!
...What have I gotten myself into?
